sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118026
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part consists of dxs (deoxyxylulose phosphate synthase, rate controlling step of terpenoid synthesis in bacteria) plus crtE (geranygeranyl pyrophosphate synthase, which generates the 20 carbon precursor for synthesis of phytoene, which in turn is the precursor for carotenoids).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: dxs is from Escherichia coli; crtE is from Pantoea ananatis (formerly known as Erwinia uredovora).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J15001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: strong synthetic E. coli ribosome binding site with SacI site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a strong synthetic E. coli ribosome binding site. It is synthesised as two complementary oligonucleotides rather than being incorporated into a biobrick plasmid. It incorporates a SacI site overlapping the XbaI site, which is preserved when it is added to any other biobrick. This allows easy detection of the RBS after it has been added upstream of a biobrick coding sequence in a plasmid vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Note the presence of a SacI site overlapping the XbaI site, which is preserved when this biobrick is added to any other biobrick. At the time of writing, this biobrick is added as a short piece of DNA composed of two complementary oligonucleotides rather than being incorporated into a biobrick cloning vector by itself. It can be added upstream of a biobrick coding sequence, and its presence can easily be detected in miniprep DNA on a gel by using a SacI-SpeI or similar digest.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: dxs
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of dxs from Escherichia coli JM109. It encodes 1-deoxyxylulose-5-phosphate synthase, thiamine-requiring, which catalyses teh first step in the biosynthesis of terpenoids. Overexpression of dxs has been reported to increase yields of carotenoids and other terpenoids [add reference here].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Synthetic ribosome binding site added by Son of Babel procedure
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a 4bp synthetic ribosome binding site which can be added by fusion PCR using a reverse primer and the Son of Babel cloning system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Hall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part can be added by fusion PCR using a Son of Babel reverse primer.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I742151
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: crtE (geranylgeranyl pyrophosphate synthase) from Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087. Part of the carotenoid biosynthesis parthway.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Chris French
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321). Accession: D90087.
